WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:13.972 --> 00:00:16.098
- Robby.
- Yep.

3
00:00:16.099 --> 00:00:18.225
Cellulitis
on the dorsum of the foot.

4
00:00:18.226 --> 00:00:20.227
now spreading up the leg.

5
00:00:20.228 --> 00:00:21.437
Hello. I'm Dr. Robby.

6
00:00:21.438 --> 00:00:23.147
Mind if I take a look?

7
00:00:23.148 --> 00:00:25.232
How long do you think
this is gonna take?

8
00:00:25.233 --> 00:00:26.735
I took an early lunch break.

9
00:00:27.944 --> 00:00:29.153
I don't know that you're gonna

10
00:00:29.154 --> 00:00:31.030
make it back to work today.

11
00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:32.698
Erythema and warmth
halfway up her knee.

12
00:00:32.699 --> 00:00:33.824
When did you see her. Donnie?

13
00:00:33.825 --> 00:00:36.285
He didn't. I did.

14
00:00:36.286 --> 00:00:37.786
- When?
- About four hours ago.

15
00:00:37.787 --> 00:00:39.204
Gave her a dose of Keflex.

16
00:00:39.205 --> 00:00:40.748
told her to come back
if things got worse.

17
00:00:40.749 --> 00:00:42.708
Things have
definitely gotten worse.

18
00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:43.709
Dana. what's open?

19
00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:45.169
Trauma Two.

20
00:00:45.170 --> 00:00:46.670
Jesse. can you get her
started in Trauma Two

21
00:00:46.671 --> 00:00:47.963
with some vanco
and blood cultures. please?

22
00:00:47.964 --> 00:00:49.423
- Got it. boss.
- I'm coming with.

23
00:00:49.424 --> 00:00:51.508
Suit yourself.

24
00:00:51.509 --> 00:00:54.803
Santos. you want in
on Trauma Two?

25
00:00:54.804 --> 00:00:57.765
Too much charting.
too little time.

26
00:00:57.766 --> 00:01:01.518
62-year-old male presents
with chief complaint

27
00:01:01.519 --> 00:01:02.686
of left lower back pain.

28
00:01:02.687 --> 00:01:04.146
- Considered the diagnosis...
- Hey.

29
00:01:04.147 --> 00:01:05.355
Oh. Jesus Christ.

30
00:01:05.356 --> 00:01:06.815
I'm charting.

31
00:01:06.816 --> 00:01:08.234
Sorry.

32
00:01:09.319 --> 00:01:10.903
Did I do something wrong?

33
00:01:10.904 --> 00:01:12.654
Besides interrupting me?
Probably.

34
00:01:12.655 --> 00:01:14.281
Then I apologize.

35
00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:17.910
I know that second year
of residency can be stressful.

36
00:01:17.911 --> 00:01:21.121
so if there's anything
I can do to help you...

37
00:01:21.122 --> 00:01:22.372
like stop talking.

38
00:01:22.373 --> 00:01:24.708
- That's a great idea.
- Yeah.

39
00:01:24.709 --> 00:01:28.879
Considered the diagnosis of
aortic aneurysm or dissection.

40
00:01:28.880 --> 00:01:30.589
Got a new one for you in 13.

41
00:01:30.590 --> 00:01:33.217
I'm 20 charts behind.
and the new attending

42
00:01:33.218 --> 00:01:34.384
is threatening to make me repeat

43
00:01:34.385 --> 00:01:35.511
a year if I can't catch up.

44
00:01:35.512 --> 00:01:36.762
Cry me a river.

45
00:01:36.763 --> 00:01:37.888
Old lady with bad
abdominal pain.

46
00:01:37.889 --> 00:01:39.056
Somebody's gotta see her.

47
00:01:39.057 --> 00:01:40.557
Dana. please do me a solid.

48
00:01:40.558 --> 00:01:42.226
Holiday weekend.

49
00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:43.852
Westbridge is down. and our
waiting room's on overdrive.

50
00:01:43.853 --> 00:01:45.229
I'm sorry. but your charting's
gonna have to wait

51
00:01:45.230 --> 00:01:47.689
until after your shift.

52
00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:49.149
Ogilvie.

53
00:01:49.150 --> 00:01:53.028
Dr. Santos needs you to pick up
a new patient in 13.

54
00:01:53.029 --> 00:01:56.907
Y-yes. ma'am.
I'm on it.

55
00:01:56.908 --> 00:01:58.200
Chart while you supervise.

56
00:01:58.201 --> 00:01:59.911
Best I can do.

57
00:02:03.039 --> 00:02:05.999
Setting up a GoFundMe. that's
what her generation does.

58
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:07.876
That's how they
support each other.

59
00:02:07.877 --> 00:02:08.961
Doctor. tell him.

60
00:02:08.962 --> 00:02:10.546
Your wife's right.

61
00:02:10.547 --> 00:02:12.881
Staying here's gonna cost
more than we can afford.

62
00:02:12.882 --> 00:02:14.758
Look. I'm feeling better.

63
00:02:14.759 --> 00:02:16.301
I'll just leave.

64
00:02:16.302 --> 00:02:19.263
Mr. Diaz. even if your
blood sugar is back to normal.

65
00:02:19.264 --> 00:02:21.223
we have to continue
with the insulin drip

66
00:02:21.224 --> 00:02:23.142
until we clear the ketones
from your bloodstream.

67
00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:25.686
Otherwise. you could experience
electrolyte disorders.

68
00:02:25.687 --> 00:02:27.020
heart and kidney problems...

69
00:02:27.021 --> 00:02:30.566
<i>Mi amor.</i> your health
is what matters.

70
00:02:30.567 --> 00:02:32.025
I'll make you a deal.

71
00:02:32.026 --> 00:02:33.861
You agree to stay
on the insulin drip.

72
00:02:33.862 --> 00:02:35.362
and I'll go find
our case manager

73
00:02:35.363 --> 00:02:37.281
to discuss cost-cutting options
for your stay.

74
00:02:37.282 --> 00:02:38.657
Deal.

75
00:02:38.658 --> 00:02:40.909
And I'm sitting here
making sure he doesn't move.

76
00:02:40.910 --> 00:02:43.036
- You should go look for Ana.
- Mm-hmm.

77
00:02:43.037 --> 00:02:44.121
I can find her.

78
00:02:44.122 --> 00:02:45.707
BRB.

79
00:02:47.876 --> 00:02:49.084
Hanging vanco.

80
00:02:49.085 --> 00:02:50.627
What's vanco?

81
00:02:50.628 --> 00:02:53.130
A really strong antibiotic
to kill skin germs.

82
00:02:53.131 --> 00:02:55.674
- Need a hand?
- No. We got this.

83
00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:57.509
I'll just observe.

84
00:02:57.510 --> 00:02:58.969
Pretend I'm not even here.

85
00:02:58.970 --> 00:03:02.431
Let's send off a CBC.
blood cultures. and CMP.

86
00:03:02.432 --> 00:03:05.475
And also a lactic acid.
CRP. and calcitonin.

87
00:03:05.476 --> 00:03:07.561
Wait. she's not febrile.
not tachycardic.

88
00:03:07.562 --> 00:03:09.188
No evidence of SIRS.

89
00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:11.148
- Yet.
- What's SIRS?

90
00:03:11.149 --> 00:03:14.902
Systemic inflammatory
response syndrome.

91
00:03:14.903 --> 00:03:15.944
Sorry.

92
00:03:15.945 --> 00:03:17.613
An exaggerated defense response.

93
00:03:17.614 --> 00:03:18.947
A what?

94
00:03:18.948 --> 00:03:21.033
Sometimes the human body
can have an overreaction

95
00:03:21.034 --> 00:03:22.951
to an infection.
so we're gonna monitor you

96
00:03:22.952 --> 00:03:24.495
to make sure
that this does not progress.

97
00:03:27.332 --> 00:03:28.790
It's my boss.

98
00:03:28.791 --> 00:03:30.792
Sorry. I have to take this.
or he's gonna fire me.

99
00:03:30.793 --> 00:03:32.878
OK.

100
00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:34.421
Hello.

101
00:03:34.422 --> 00:03:38.050
No. I'm still at the hospital.

102
00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:39.551
Being seen right now.

103
00:03:39.552 --> 00:03:40.844
Ow.

104
00:03:40.845 --> 00:03:44.014
No. they just stuck me
with a needle.

105
00:03:44.015 --> 00:03:45.724
I don't know.

106
00:03:45.725 --> 00:03:48.143
You wanna talk to them?

107
00:03:48.144 --> 00:03:51.188
They're kind of busy right now.

108
00:03:51.189 --> 00:03:52.648
I know you are.

109
00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:54.107
Second IV's in.

110
00:03:54.108 --> 00:03:55.817
No. I'm not overreacting.

111
00:03:55.818 --> 00:03:58.153
My body's overreacting.

112
00:03:58.154 --> 00:04:00.155
Please... please don't fire me.

113
00:04:00.156 --> 00:04:01.448
I...

114
00:04:01.449 --> 00:04:02.908
This is
Dr. Michael Robinavitch.

115
00:04:02.909 --> 00:04:04.952
I am the chief
of emergency medicine at PTMC.

116
00:04:04.953 --> 00:04:06.912
If you fire her.
she will sue you.

117
00:04:06.913 --> 00:04:09.915
and I will testify
on her behalf.

118
00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:12.209
OK.

119
00:04:12.210 --> 00:04:14.087
Don't worry about it.
We got you.

120
00:04:18.967 --> 00:04:20.926
Do you know how long
Jackson's gonna be asleep?

121
00:04:20.927 --> 00:04:24.179
So there's no exact timeline
with the sedatives we gave him.

122
00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:25.889
but he should be awake soon.

123
00:04:25.890 --> 00:04:27.557
Have you spoken
to your parents yet?

124
00:04:27.558 --> 00:04:29.184
Yeah. they're on their way
back from Columbus.

125
00:04:29.185 --> 00:04:31.645
Maybe you should take
some time for yourself

126
00:04:31.646 --> 00:04:33.063
before they arrive.

127
00:04:33.064 --> 00:04:34.731
Yeah. cafeteria's
right down the hall.

128
00:04:34.732 --> 00:04:35.774
Decent grilled cheese.

129
00:04:35.775 --> 00:04:36.900
Stay away from the tuna.

130
00:04:36.901 --> 00:04:38.944
Thanks. but I'm not hungry.

131
00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:41.655
You know. I just can't believe
that a campus security guard

132
00:04:41.656 --> 00:04:43.115
tased my brother.

133
00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:44.616
Aren't they supposed
to be helping students

134
00:04:44.617 --> 00:04:46.702
and protect them.
not shoot at them?

135
00:04:46.703 --> 00:04:48.412
You have every right
to be upset.

136
00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:51.081
and you should absolutely
pursue accountability.

137
00:04:51.082 --> 00:04:53.375
But right now. we are
taking care of your brother.

138
00:04:53.376 --> 00:04:56.211
And you should really
take care of yourself.

139
00:04:56.212 --> 00:04:57.796
I... I have your number.

140
00:04:57.797 --> 00:05:00.173
I'll text you as soon as
Jackson's LP results get back

141
00:05:00.174 --> 00:05:02.384
or if he wakes up.

142
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:04.094
OK.

143
00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:05.429
OK. thank you.

144
00:05:05.430 --> 00:05:06.596
Of course.

145
00:05:06.597 --> 00:05:09.766
- Oh.
- OK.

146
00:05:09.767 --> 00:05:11.393
Hypoactive bowel sounds.

147
00:05:11.394 --> 00:05:14.271
Soft. with moderate tenderness
in the left lower quadrant.

148
00:05:14.272 --> 00:05:17.524
Mrs. Randolph. do you
take Percocet every day?

149
00:05:17.525 --> 00:05:19.443
- No.
- Huh.

150
00:05:19.444 --> 00:05:20.902
And what about your
water intake. 'cause...

151
00:05:20.903 --> 00:05:22.446
Pause.

152
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:24.614
Mrs. Randolph. you said you
don't take Percocet every day.

153
00:05:24.615 --> 00:05:26.616
but when was the last time
you took some?

154
00:05:26.617 --> 00:05:29.911
Maybe three or four times
last week.

155
00:05:29.912 --> 00:05:33.540
Assisted living had
a ballroom dance competition.

156
00:05:33.541 --> 00:05:35.751
- and I tweaked my back.
- Mm.

157
00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:39.838
Any further questions. Ogilvie?

158
00:05:39.839 --> 00:05:43.550
When was your last
bowel movement?

159
00:05:43.551 --> 00:05:46.053
I don't know.
Sometime last week.

160
00:05:46.054 --> 00:05:49.056
I've been stopped up
for at least five or six days.

161
00:05:49.057 --> 00:05:52.517
Mm-hmm. painkillers
can cause constipation.

162
00:05:52.518 --> 00:05:53.810
I know.

163
00:05:53.811 --> 00:05:56.355
That's why they put me
on a stool softener.

164
00:05:56.356 --> 00:05:57.689
and then they tried an enema.

165
00:05:57.690 --> 00:05:59.733
- And... and no movements?
- Yep.

166
00:05:59.734 --> 00:06:03.028
And then they gave me
this horrible drink.

167
00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:04.654
Mag citrate.

168
00:06:04.655 --> 00:06:05.697
Yeah.

169
00:06:05.698 --> 00:06:08.033
Mag citrate.

170
00:06:08.034 --> 00:06:09.326
Made me puke.

171
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:11.536
All right. what's next. Ogilvie?

172
00:06:11.537 --> 00:06:13.580
Let's get you an X-ray
and see how we can help you.

173
00:06:13.581 --> 00:06:14.581
Mrs. Randolph.

174
00:06:14.582 --> 00:06:16.458
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

175
00:06:16.459 --> 00:06:18.627
Differential?

176
00:06:18.628 --> 00:06:20.295
Probable stool impaction.

177
00:06:20.296 --> 00:06:21.880
But with her history
of cholecystectomy.

178
00:06:21.881 --> 00:06:23.632
it could be
small bowel obstruction.

179
00:06:23.633 --> 00:06:24.758
Or worse.

180
00:06:24.759 --> 00:06:27.010
Sigmoid volvulus?

181
00:06:27.011 --> 00:06:29.388
But that's a surgical emergency.

182
00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:30.931
Wouldn't she have tons of pain?

183
00:06:30.932 --> 00:06:34.394
Not always. especially when
you're in your 80s.

184
00:06:40.024 --> 00:06:41.650
I am getting concerned.

185
00:06:41.651 --> 00:06:44.236
This is a millimeter
past the line.

186
00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:45.612
Or my line was sloppy.

187
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:47.155
- Any increase in pain?
- Oh.

188
00:06:47.156 --> 00:06:49.741
OK. sorry.
Let's try four morphine.

189
00:06:49.742 --> 00:06:51.076
White count's only 10.000.

190
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:53.120
It'd be over 12.000 for SIRS.

191
00:06:53.121 --> 00:06:54.913
There are other criteria.

192
00:06:54.914 --> 00:06:56.373
Still afebrile.

193
00:06:56.374 --> 00:06:57.958
Did you ask about
past history of MRSA?

194
00:06:57.959 --> 00:06:59.751
Not specifically. but she's
never been hospitalized.

195
00:06:59.752 --> 00:07:01.253
Any evidence
of an immunocompromised state?

196
00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:02.504
- No. she's healthy.
- Steroid use?

197
00:07:02.505 --> 00:07:03.505
Never.

198
00:07:03.506 --> 00:07:05.048
Maximum heart rate's only 89.

199
00:07:05.049 --> 00:07:06.216
Is that OK?

200
00:07:06.217 --> 00:07:08.301
That's good. very good.

201
00:07:08.302 --> 00:07:09.302
Stay with her.

202
00:07:09.303 --> 00:07:10.887
Monitor her closely.

203
00:07:10.888 --> 00:07:12.722
If there's any change in her
condition. come find me.

204
00:07:12.723 --> 00:07:13.850
I mean any change.

205
00:07:16.978 --> 00:07:19.646
Roxie Hamler. 42.
home hospice patient

206
00:07:19.647 --> 00:07:21.231
with a history of lung cancer.

207
00:07:21.232 --> 00:07:24.443
New-onset tonic-clonic seizure
with right lower leg pain.

208
00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:26.487
She hit it on the coffee table.

209
00:07:28.197 --> 00:07:30.031
Initially nonverbal.
now coming around.

210
00:07:30.032 --> 00:07:31.533
That's normal after a seizure.

211
00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:33.118
- Hi. I'm Dr. Al-Hashimi.
- Do you need a hand?

212
00:07:33.119 --> 00:07:34.911
- Nope. we got it.
- She hit her head?

213
00:07:34.912 --> 00:07:36.079
No.
I was there.

214
00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:37.706
- I caught her.
- No IV?

215
00:07:37.707 --> 00:07:38.999
Couldn't get one in.

216
00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:40.500
Gave her four of IM versed
for the seizure.

217
00:07:40.501 --> 00:07:42.043
- 25 of fent for the pain.
- OK.

218
00:07:42.044 --> 00:07:43.920
- Dana. where to?
- Trauma One.

219
00:07:43.921 --> 00:07:45.172
This way.

220
00:07:45.173 --> 00:07:47.507
Haven't seen you guys
in a hot minute.

221
00:07:47.508 --> 00:07:50.093
Pickup from SCI Jones Forge.

222
00:07:50.094 --> 00:07:51.595
Was supposed to go
to Westbridge but got

223
00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:52.596
diverted to you.

224
00:07:52.597 --> 00:07:54.014
Yeah. you and everybody else.

225
00:07:54.015 --> 00:07:55.557
Princess. I need you
pivot to Central 9.

226
00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:56.892
Got it.

227
00:07:56.893 --> 00:07:58.602
Gus Varney. 54.
victim of assault

228
00:07:58.603 --> 00:07:59.978
with diffuse blunt trauma.

229
00:07:59.979 --> 00:08:01.980
He's got bruising to the face.
the right chest.

230
00:08:01.981 --> 00:08:03.648
10-centimeter laceration
to the left arm.

231
00:08:03.649 --> 00:08:05.233
BP's 136 over 84. pulse 102.

232
00:08:05.234 --> 00:08:07.986
good sats. 95 on room air.

233
00:08:07.987 --> 00:08:09.696
How you feeling there.
Mr. Varney?

234
00:08:09.697 --> 00:08:11.198
- Fucking hurts.
- Where?

235
00:08:11.199 --> 00:08:13.533
- Everywhere.
- I am Dr. Robby.

236
00:08:13.534 --> 00:08:14.826
This is Dr. Al-Hashimi.

237
00:08:14.827 --> 00:08:16.286
We'll get you
something for the pain.

238
00:08:16.287 --> 00:08:17.829
I've got a progressing
cellulitis in Trauma Two.

239
00:08:17.830 --> 00:08:19.456
- Go. I'm good.
- Thank you.

240
00:08:19.457 --> 00:08:21.500
Gus. do you know who hurt you?

241
00:08:21.501 --> 00:08:24.169
One of the fine. upstanding
citizens of cell block 6.

242
00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:27.088
It's a deep lac
through the muscle fascia.

243
00:08:27.089 --> 00:08:28.632
Can we get the cuffs off
once he settles?

244
00:08:28.633 --> 00:08:29.799
Not a chance.

245
00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:31.760
Orange jumpsuit.
He's cuffed for a reason.

246
00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:33.804
Let's go.

247
00:08:44.190 --> 00:08:47.734
OK. everyone. on my count.

248
00:08:47.735 --> 00:08:49.361
1. 2...

249
00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:50.821
Hold on.

250
00:08:54.450 --> 00:08:58.036
- Go.
- 1. 2. 3.

251
00:08:58.037 --> 00:08:59.538
Mel. E-FAST.

252
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:01.122
Whitaker. primary assessment.

253
00:09:01.123 --> 00:09:02.333
On it.

254
00:09:07.463 --> 00:09:08.672
Oh. weird bruise.

255
00:09:08.673 --> 00:09:09.965
Did he fall on something?

256
00:09:09.966 --> 00:09:11.466
Footprint. got stomped.

257
00:09:11.467 --> 00:09:13.386
Jesus.

258
00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:16.388
Is it... is that necessary?

259
00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:18.557
Afraid so.

260
00:09:18.558 --> 00:09:21.184
Airway's patent.

261
00:09:21.185 --> 00:09:23.937
Good lung sliding on the left.

262
00:09:23.938 --> 00:09:25.146
Sorry.

263
00:09:25.147 --> 00:09:26.439
Good on the right. too.

264
00:09:26.440 --> 00:09:27.816
How are the lungs?

265
00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:28.942
Good breath sounds.

266
00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:31.695
- No crepitus.
- No effusion.

267
00:09:31.696 --> 00:09:34.990
Pulse ox 97. BP 118 over 78.
heart rate 112.

268
00:09:34.991 --> 00:09:36.366
Tachycardic from the pain.

269
00:09:36.367 --> 00:09:37.909
Start with four of morphine.
Repeat prn.

270
00:09:37.910 --> 00:09:38.910
On it.

271
00:09:38.911 --> 00:09:41.037
OK.
Swollen mandible.

272
00:09:41.038 --> 00:09:42.455
Open your mouth for me. Gus.

273
00:09:42.456 --> 00:09:44.291
Little wider.

274
00:09:44.292 --> 00:09:45.542
Can't.

275
00:09:45.543 --> 00:09:46.918
Whitaker. you know
the tongue blade exam?

276
00:09:46.919 --> 00:09:48.378
Yeah.

277
00:09:48.379 --> 00:09:49.838
It's a great test
for mandible fracture.

278
00:09:49.839 --> 00:09:52.967
Gus. bite down hard
on this for me.

279
00:09:55.261 --> 00:09:56.636
Sorry. Gus.

280
00:09:56.637 --> 00:09:58.763
Positive test.

281
00:09:58.764 --> 00:10:00.307
No free fluid in the belly.

282
00:10:00.308 --> 00:10:01.308
Any idea how long
this will take?

283
00:10:01.309 --> 00:10:02.684
Too soon to tell.

284
00:10:02.685 --> 00:10:03.768
Whitaker. your assessment?

285
00:10:03.769 --> 00:10:05.186
Fractured left mandible.

286
00:10:05.187 --> 00:10:07.355
multiple rib fractures.

287
00:10:07.356 --> 00:10:08.857
Complex forearm lac.

288
00:10:08.858 --> 00:10:10.859
OK. log roll to the left.
then pan scan.

289
00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:12.819
Where were you when
Mr. Varney got assaulted?

290
00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:14.404
I just move 'em.
I don't get to know 'em.

291
00:10:14.405 --> 00:10:16.156
CT's ready for us.

292
00:10:16.157 --> 00:10:17.991
Cycling the BP.

293
00:10:17.992 --> 00:10:20.660
OK. this redness is now
a centimeter over that line.

294
00:10:20.661 --> 00:10:22.162
and this might be
a bulla forming.

295
00:10:22.163 --> 00:10:23.455
The vanco takes
a little time to work.

296
00:10:23.456 --> 00:10:27.000
Vital signs are still stable.
122 over 78.

297
00:10:27.001 --> 00:10:28.084
I got it.

298
00:10:28.085 --> 00:10:31.087
How are you feeling. Debbie?

299
00:10:31.088 --> 00:10:32.756
I'm feeling a little warm.

300
00:10:32.757 --> 00:10:34.174
That can happen with vanco.

301
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.134
Thanks. man.

302
00:10:36.135 --> 00:10:39.179
Lactic acid 4.2.

303
00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:40.972
- OK.
- What's wrong?

304
00:10:40.973 --> 00:10:43.683
That can be a sign
of a more serious infection.

305
00:10:43.684 --> 00:10:45.310
but the good news is.
we know what to do.

306
00:10:45.311 --> 00:10:49.022
Jesse. 2 liters of LR wide open.

307
00:10:49.023 --> 00:10:50.482
This is severe sepsis.

308
00:10:50.483 --> 00:10:52.108
I know. but at 7:00 AM.
it was a simple cellulitis.

309
00:10:52.109 --> 00:10:53.735
Anyone would have
given her Keflex.

310
00:10:53.736 --> 00:10:55.737
We could add carbapenem
or Zosyn to broaden

311
00:10:55.738 --> 00:10:56.780
our antibiotic coverage.

312
00:10:56.781 --> 00:10:57.947
OK. I got it.

313
00:10:57.948 --> 00:10:59.366
Thanks.

314
00:10:59.367 --> 00:11:02.369
Jesse. 1 gram meropenem.
900 milligrams clinda.

315
00:11:02.370 --> 00:11:04.412
and page Dr. Garcia. please.

316
00:11:04.413 --> 00:11:05.830
What's going on?

317
00:11:05.831 --> 00:11:07.290
We're adding new antibiotics.

318
00:11:07.291 --> 00:11:08.708
It's serious?

319
00:11:08.709 --> 00:11:09.918
We wanna get ahead
of it and make sure

320
00:11:09.919 --> 00:11:11.712
it doesn't become serious.

321
00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:14.464
What else can I do?

322
00:11:14.465 --> 00:11:15.632
I think you've done enough.

323
00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:16.759
You can go.

324
00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:21.513
All good in there?

325
00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:22.639
Code sepsis.

326
00:11:22.640 --> 00:11:23.973
Stable for the moment.

327
00:11:23.974 --> 00:11:25.266
How about you?

328
00:11:25.267 --> 00:11:27.644
Perfect vitals.
E-FAST negative. off to CT.

329
00:11:27.645 --> 00:11:28.853
Good.

330
00:11:28.854 --> 00:11:30.438
Keep me posted.

331
00:11:30.439 --> 00:11:31.732
Ditto.

332
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:36.778
How's it going?

333
00:11:36.779 --> 00:11:38.780
Great. if you ignore
the hot mess in chairs.

334
00:11:38.781 --> 00:11:40.699
Any update on our
little baby Jane Doe?

335
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:42.701
Security's reviewing
the CCTV from last night

336
00:11:42.702 --> 00:11:43.911
and this morning.

337
00:11:46.288 --> 00:11:47.747
You two kiss and make up yet?

338
00:11:47.748 --> 00:11:49.332
I think someone needs
to smoke a cigarette.

339
00:11:49.333 --> 00:11:50.750
I'm trying to quit.

340
00:11:50.751 --> 00:11:52.293
Why don't you quit
when I'm on my trip?

341
00:11:52.294 --> 00:11:53.545
Everyone's glad
to have you back.

342
00:11:53.546 --> 00:11:56.006
- Asshole.
- Well. not everyone.

343
00:11:57.508 --> 00:11:59.968
Hey. you want in
on this betting board?

344
00:11:59.969 --> 00:12:02.929
Look. all you gotta do is
pick why Westbridge went down.

345
00:12:02.930 --> 00:12:04.556
how many of their patients
we're gonna get.

346
00:12:04.557 --> 00:12:06.182
and when they'll
be back in action.

347
00:12:06.183 --> 00:12:08.935
Hey. already up to $500.

348
00:12:08.936 --> 00:12:11.271
Oh. ah. gotta pass.

349
00:12:11.272 --> 00:12:13.440
Still catching up
on rehab bills.

350
00:12:13.441 --> 00:12:15.901
Respect.

351
00:12:17.486 --> 00:12:18.653
All right.

352
00:12:18.654 --> 00:12:20.363
What's the rules
on me changing my bet?

353
00:12:20.364 --> 00:12:22.491
Only if you double down.

354
00:12:24.618 --> 00:12:25.995
Sinkhole.

355
00:12:28.664 --> 00:12:32.167
You watch too many movies. man.

356
00:12:32.168 --> 00:12:35.253
Considered the diagnosis
of aortic aneurysm

357
00:12:35.254 --> 00:12:37.505
or dissection. but the
point-of-care ultrasound was...

358
00:12:37.506 --> 00:12:40.091
You done want that
gridlocked granny?

359
00:12:40.092 --> 00:12:42.010
Ordered an acute
abdominal series

360
00:12:42.011 --> 00:12:43.261
to rule out obstruction.

361
00:12:43.262 --> 00:12:44.512
- Still waiting on the X-rays.
- Great.

362
00:12:44.513 --> 00:12:45.638
Then you're free
to treat our latest

363
00:12:45.639 --> 00:12:46.848
and greatest in South 16.

364
00:12:46.849 --> 00:12:49.642
Oh. come on. D.
it's like. every time

365
00:12:49.643 --> 00:12:51.227
I get a moment to chart.
I barely get

366
00:12:51.228 --> 00:12:53.938
- a sentence out before I get...
- Interrupted?

367
00:12:53.939 --> 00:12:55.982
Sucks to be you.
but trust me. it sucks worse

368
00:12:55.983 --> 00:12:57.901
for the poor gal in 16.

369
00:12:57.902 --> 00:13:00.653
I'm beginning to think
you enjoy torturing me.

370
00:13:00.654 --> 00:13:02.781
Perks of the job.

371
00:13:02.782 --> 00:13:04.074
Ogilvie. let's go.

372
00:13:07.703 --> 00:13:10.414
Hold out your hand. Louie.

373
00:13:11.373 --> 00:13:13.082
A little shaky.

374
00:13:13.083 --> 00:13:14.083
No surprise.

375
00:13:14.084 --> 00:13:16.252
I've been here since 4:00 AM.

376
00:13:16.253 --> 00:13:17.629
We can get you
something for that.

377
00:13:17.630 --> 00:13:18.963
Or I can take care of it myself

378
00:13:18.964 --> 00:13:21.090
if you cut me loose right now.

379
00:13:21.091 --> 00:13:23.259
Let's get Louie
50 milligrams of Librium.

380
00:13:23.260 --> 00:13:24.804
I'll put in the order.

381
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:29.683
I will get it from the PDS.

382
00:13:33.229 --> 00:13:35.814
I'm already assigned
as Louie's treating physician.

383
00:13:35.815 --> 00:13:38.233
Just makes sense
that I put it in.

384
00:13:38.234 --> 00:13:40.319
Yeah. Yeah. yeah.
Of course.

385
00:13:45.449 --> 00:13:47.951
Any changes
with our septic waitress?

386
00:13:47.952 --> 00:13:49.077
Not yet.

387
00:13:49.078 --> 00:13:50.161
Wait. if you have a second. I...

388
00:13:50.162 --> 00:13:51.329
I don't.

389
00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:52.747
But the point-of-care ultrasound

390
00:13:52.748 --> 00:13:54.165
was negative for both.

391
00:13:54.166 --> 00:13:56.584
I considered the diagnosis
of cauda equina syndrome.

392
00:13:56.585 --> 00:13:59.712
You writing the great
American novel?

393
00:13:59.713 --> 00:14:01.673
Charting and supervising.

394
00:14:01.674 --> 00:14:02.715
It's Dana's idea.

395
00:14:02.716 --> 00:14:04.259
Who's the lucky patient?

396
00:14:04.260 --> 00:14:06.135
Unhoused woman with a bad cough.

397
00:14:06.136 --> 00:14:07.929
Ogilvie's all over it.

398
00:14:07.930 --> 00:14:09.305
OK.

399
00:14:09.306 --> 00:14:10.849
Say "eee."

400
00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.600
Eee.

401
00:14:12.601 --> 00:14:14.352
OK. deep breath in.

402
00:14:14.353 --> 00:14:16.271
Blow it out real hard.

403
00:14:16.272 --> 00:14:18.022
You haven't heard
enough already?

404
00:14:18.023 --> 00:14:21.986
I need to check for wheezing
with forced exhalation.

405
00:14:25.239 --> 00:14:27.198
Fucking cough is killing me.

406
00:14:27.199 --> 00:14:28.783
You smoke. Mrs. Yardley?

407
00:14:28.784 --> 00:14:30.994
Yeah. but I haven't been able to

408
00:14:30.995 --> 00:14:32.412
for a couple days
'cause of this cough.

409
00:14:32.413 --> 00:14:34.664
Mm.
You ever consider quitting?

410
00:14:34.665 --> 00:14:38.085
You ever considered
minding your own business?

411
00:14:42.006 --> 00:14:44.257
Well. the good news
is that your test from earlier

412
00:14:44.258 --> 00:14:46.467
came back negative for both
COVID and influenza.

413
00:14:46.468 --> 00:14:48.136
but I'm gonna order
a chest X-ray

414
00:14:48.137 --> 00:14:49.679
so that we can see what's
really going on in those lungs.

415
00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:51.599
You got time to let us do that?

416
00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:55.852
Where the fuck else
you think I gotta be?

417
00:14:55.853 --> 00:14:57.645
And we're in.

418
00:14:57.646 --> 00:14:59.314
3 grams Keppra over 10 minutes.

419
00:14:59.315 --> 00:15:01.024
That'll prevent another seizure.

420
00:15:01.025 --> 00:15:02.108
Thank you.

421
00:15:02.109 --> 00:15:04.027
Nobody can ever
get an IV in her.

422
00:15:04.028 --> 00:15:05.987
Yeah. midline cath
is the way to go

423
00:15:05.988 --> 00:15:07.614
when your veins are shot.

424
00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:12.201
Tachy to 114. BP 94 over 70.
sat 91 on 2 liters.

425
00:15:12.202 --> 00:15:14.913
- OK.
- Cold.

426
00:15:14.914 --> 00:15:18.374
Is it possible to get her
a blanket and some socks?

427
00:15:18.375 --> 00:15:20.126
Can do.

428
00:15:20.127 --> 00:15:22.670
When was she diagnosed?

429
00:15:22.671 --> 00:15:24.631
Seven years ago.

430
00:15:24.632 --> 00:15:27.216
Resected a lobe.

431
00:15:27.217 --> 00:15:29.761
Four cycles of platinum chemo
gave us a couple good years.

432
00:15:29.762 --> 00:15:32.221
but then it spread to the bones.

433
00:15:32.222 --> 00:15:34.432
Has she had radiation therapy?

434
00:15:34.433 --> 00:15:36.893
Shrunk down the mets.
but they're still there.

435
00:15:36.894 --> 00:15:38.853
That's why you're
at hospice at home.

436
00:15:38.854 --> 00:15:39.854
Yep.

437
00:15:39.855 --> 00:15:41.898
I'm sorry.

438
00:15:41.899 --> 00:15:43.191
Me too.

439
00:15:43.192 --> 00:15:45.777
Ah.

440
00:15:45.778 --> 00:15:46.903
Sorry.

441
00:15:46.904 --> 00:15:48.446
You have kids?

442
00:15:48.447 --> 00:15:50.907
Yeah. two boys.

443
00:15:50.908 --> 00:15:52.992
15 and 9.

444
00:15:52.993 --> 00:15:54.577
My son's 12.

445
00:15:54.578 --> 00:15:56.788
Goes fast.

446
00:15:56.789 --> 00:15:58.623
Too fast.

447
00:15:58.624 --> 00:16:03.252
Swelling and bruising
over the distal tibia.

448
00:16:03.253 --> 00:16:05.880
50 of fentanyl
once her systolic's over 100.

449
00:16:05.881 --> 00:16:08.425
What do you usually
take for pain?

450
00:16:11.428 --> 00:16:14.639
MS Contin. 30 milligrams
twice a day.

451
00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:17.058
oxycodone for breakthrough.
and sublingual Actiq

452
00:16:17.059 --> 00:16:20.853
for when it gets really bad.

453
00:16:20.854 --> 00:16:22.021
That's a lot.

454
00:16:22.022 --> 00:16:23.815
You handle her pain meds?

455
00:16:23.816 --> 00:16:24.899
Sometimes.

456
00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:26.776
All the time.

457
00:16:26.777 --> 00:16:29.654
A hospice nurse comes by
a few times a week.

458
00:16:29.655 --> 00:16:32.031
but I was alone
when she had the seizure.

459
00:16:32.032 --> 00:16:33.992
They told us
that it could happen.

460
00:16:33.993 --> 00:16:35.576
but she couldn't breathe.

461
00:16:35.577 --> 00:16:40.039
And I freaked out.
and I called 911.

462
00:16:40.040 --> 00:16:42.333
I'm so sorry.

463
00:16:42.334 --> 00:16:46.088
I'm sorry.

464
00:16:55.764 --> 00:16:58.933
Due to your family income.
you make too much

465
00:16:58.934 --> 00:17:00.810
to be eligible for either PENNIE

466
00:17:00.811 --> 00:17:03.229
or the hospital's
"charity care."

467
00:17:03.230 --> 00:17:05.356
But we can't afford
health-care premiums.

468
00:17:05.357 --> 00:17:08.151
It's unfortunately
very common for people

469
00:17:08.152 --> 00:17:09.444
to fall between the cracks.

470
00:17:09.445 --> 00:17:11.571
It's an imperfect system.

471
00:17:11.572 --> 00:17:13.740
Can PTMC help
with the costs in any way?

472
00:17:13.741 --> 00:17:16.200
We can offer
financial assistance.

473
00:17:16.201 --> 00:17:18.036
You'd pay the same that Medicare

474
00:17:18.037 --> 00:17:19.662
and Medicaid would pay.

475
00:17:19.663 --> 00:17:20.788
How much is that?

476
00:17:20.789 --> 00:17:24.709
You pay 60%. we cover 40%.

477
00:17:24.710 --> 00:17:26.085
Thank you.

478
00:17:26.086 --> 00:17:27.921
Uh-huh.

479
00:17:29.131 --> 00:17:31.215
Where have you been?

480
00:17:31.216 --> 00:17:33.718
- How are you doing?
- I'm sorry. <i>mijita.</i>

481
00:17:33.719 --> 00:17:36.804
You were being thoughtful.
and I just blew up.

482
00:17:36.805 --> 00:17:39.724
Well. Ms. Noelle was just
telling us that the hospital

483
00:17:39.725 --> 00:17:41.434
is gonna give us a big discount.

484
00:17:41.435 --> 00:17:44.103
We can knock 40%
off your final bill.

485
00:17:44.104 --> 00:17:46.064
- That's great.
- Mm-hmm.

486
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:47.940
I stay here for a few days.

487
00:17:47.941 --> 00:17:50.152
my bill could be
over $100.000. right?

488
00:17:51.862 --> 00:17:53.613
Yes. unfortunately.

489
00:17:53.614 --> 00:17:55.698
It could end up being lower.

490
00:17:55.699 --> 00:17:58.117
depending on your level
of needed care.

491
00:17:58.118 --> 00:18:00.119
Or higher?

492
00:18:00.120 --> 00:18:04.082
So we would still
have to pay $60.000?

493
00:18:04.083 --> 00:18:05.625
Which we don't have.

494
00:18:05.626 --> 00:18:07.835
He has to stay here
to get better. right?

495
00:18:07.836 --> 00:18:10.213
- Yes.
- No.

496
00:18:10.214 --> 00:18:11.464
Excuse me?

497
00:18:11.465 --> 00:18:13.674
I mean. not necessarily.

498
00:18:13.675 --> 00:18:16.344
Couldn't we just admit him
to med-surg instead of ICU?

499
00:18:16.345 --> 00:18:18.179
Wouldn't that be a lot cheaper?

500
00:18:18.180 --> 00:18:20.306
Med-surg won't accept him
with an insulin drip.

501
00:18:20.307 --> 00:18:22.100
Usually true.

502
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:25.770
But let me talk to the charge
nurse upstairs. and I'll...

503
00:18:25.771 --> 00:18:26.938
I'll see what she says.

504
00:18:26.939 --> 00:18:28.398
Thank you.

505
00:18:30.400 --> 00:18:32.443
Food poisoning in the hall's
asking to leave.

506
00:18:32.444 --> 00:18:34.487
wants to take her kids
to the water park.

507
00:18:34.488 --> 00:18:37.031
Those places are cesspools.

508
00:18:37.032 --> 00:18:38.533
Preaching to the choir.

509
00:18:38.534 --> 00:18:40.159
If she's feeling fine
on Zofran. she's good to go.

510
00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:41.619
All right.

511
00:18:41.620 --> 00:18:43.538
Louie's in South 15.
Meds are coming down.

512
00:18:43.539 --> 00:18:45.540
Another couple hours of
monitoring. and he can broom.

513
00:18:45.541 --> 00:18:46.833
Straight to the liquor store.

514
00:18:46.834 --> 00:18:47.959
Don't pass "go."

515
00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:48.960
What about that clamshell case

516
00:18:48.961 --> 00:18:50.419
that went up... anything?

517
00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:52.380
Out of surgery.
in recovery. still sedated.

518
00:18:52.381 --> 00:18:54.298
Good.
Keep me posted on that.

519
00:18:54.299 --> 00:18:55.634
Will do.

520
00:18:57.845 --> 00:18:59.178
Three times in one day.

521
00:18:59.179 --> 00:19:00.763
To what do we owe the pleasure?

522
00:19:00.764 --> 00:19:02.473
I came down for a consult

523
00:19:02.474 --> 00:19:04.892
and to persuade Ahmad
to start a new betting board.

524
00:19:04.893 --> 00:19:06.477
Why. is the Westbridge board
full already?

525
00:19:06.478 --> 00:19:08.521
Mm-hmm. was gonna ask him
to start one about you

526
00:19:08.522 --> 00:19:10.815
and your midlife crisis trip.

527
00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:12.817
I give it four weeks.

528
00:19:12.818 --> 00:19:15.361
Seven. tops.

529
00:19:15.362 --> 00:19:16.612
Ye of little faith.

530
00:19:16.613 --> 00:19:19.365
Not about faith. just facts.

531
00:19:19.366 --> 00:19:20.658
Facts?

532
00:19:20.659 --> 00:19:22.577
Based on my experience.
you're a seven-week-itch

533
00:19:22.578 --> 00:19:24.036
kind of guy.

534
00:19:24.037 --> 00:19:26.247
Hey. Robby. med student's
got a pickleball player

535
00:19:26.248 --> 00:19:28.207
in the North Hall
with possible Achilles rupture.

536
00:19:28.208 --> 00:19:29.208
asking for your opinion.

537
00:19:29.209 --> 00:19:30.793
Thank you. Perlah.

538
00:19:30.794 --> 00:19:32.880
At least somebody down here
has a little faith in me.

539
00:19:35.549 --> 00:19:38.259
You know what Motorcycle Mike's
sabbatical is really about?

540
00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:41.137
I never try to guess what's
going on in that head of his.

541
00:19:41.138 --> 00:19:44.348
Three months being
on the open road by himself.

542
00:19:44.349 --> 00:19:46.517
Man can't stand to be alone
for more than a few hours.

543
00:19:46.518 --> 00:19:49.562
He sleeps with the TV on
in his bedroom.

544
00:19:49.563 --> 00:19:52.357
I really don't think
I needed to know that.

545
00:19:53.817 --> 00:19:56.986
Look. maybe he's looking
for something new

546
00:19:56.987 --> 00:19:59.906
or trying to outrun
some old ghosts.

547
00:19:59.907 --> 00:20:03.201
Well. I hope he finds
what he's looking for.

548
00:20:03.202 --> 00:20:05.369
Man deserves some peace.

549
00:20:05.370 --> 00:20:06.746
Amen.

550
00:20:06.747 --> 00:20:09.415
I considered the diagnosis
of cauda equina syndrome.

551
00:20:09.416 --> 00:20:11.250
but the motor and sensory exam

552
00:20:11.251 --> 00:20:13.628
were both intact
in the sacral nerve root...

553
00:20:13.629 --> 00:20:14.962
Our unhoused cougher
has pneumonia.

554
00:20:14.963 --> 00:20:17.840
I'm cursed. fucking cursed.

555
00:20:17.841 --> 00:20:19.342
Fuck.

556
00:20:19.343 --> 00:20:21.093
What?

557
00:20:21.094 --> 00:20:23.512
That is a cavitary lesion
in the right upper lobe.

558
00:20:23.513 --> 00:20:25.306
Active TB.

559
00:20:25.307 --> 00:20:27.642
What's next?

560
00:20:27.643 --> 00:20:29.227
AFB stain to confirm.

561
00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:31.771
move her to a negative airflow
room. start her on meds.

562
00:20:31.772 --> 00:20:33.898
Call infection control
and public health.

563
00:20:33.899 --> 00:20:36.192
And now you get
to sign in as a patient

564
00:20:36.193 --> 00:20:38.653
and get your blood drawn
for a QuantiFERON Gold.

565
00:20:38.654 --> 00:20:40.655
It's too soon to be positive.

566
00:20:40.656 --> 00:20:41.822
Yeah. but you were exposed.

567
00:20:41.823 --> 00:20:43.449
You need a baseline test

568
00:20:43.450 --> 00:20:46.661
and then again in eight weeks
to see if you convert.

569
00:20:46.662 --> 00:20:47.995
And if I do?

570
00:20:47.996 --> 00:20:50.122
Then meds every day
for three or four months

571
00:20:50.123 --> 00:20:53.000
with regular blood tests
to check for toxicity.

572
00:20:53.001 --> 00:20:54.335
- Jesus.
- All right.

573
00:20:54.336 --> 00:20:55.836
Let Dana know what's up.

574
00:20:55.837 --> 00:20:58.840
And for the love of God.
mask up when you move her.

575
00:21:07.391 --> 00:21:09.600
- Dr. Langdon.
- Hey. man. Alex.

576
00:21:09.601 --> 00:21:10.727
Let's take a look.

577
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:16.315
Ah.

578
00:21:16.316 --> 00:21:17.316
Is it bad?

579
00:21:17.317 --> 00:21:18.859
It's not good.

580
00:21:18.860 --> 00:21:21.487
Sorry. your chart says
you were burned with dry ice?

581
00:21:21.488 --> 00:21:23.531
- What happened?
- My jack-off brother.

582
00:21:23.532 --> 00:21:25.116
Does he not like you?

583
00:21:25.117 --> 00:21:28.744
I asked him to do it.
just not like this exactly.

584
00:21:28.745 --> 00:21:30.329
What? Why?

585
00:21:30.330 --> 00:21:31.998
He was gonna brand me
like I branded him.

586
00:21:31.999 --> 00:21:33.833
Branded? Like cattle?

587
00:21:33.834 --> 00:21:36.961
Instead of hot branding.
you stick the iron in dry ice.

588
00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:39.922
let it get super cold. and then
you put it on your skin.

589
00:21:39.923 --> 00:21:41.757
Cool. huh?

590
00:21:41.758 --> 00:21:42.800
You're stupid.

591
00:21:42.801 --> 00:21:44.051
Let's get some LET on this.

592
00:21:44.052 --> 00:21:45.762
I'll get some snips to debride.

593
00:21:48.265 --> 00:21:49.932
You good?

594
00:21:49.933 --> 00:21:52.268
Yeah. Yeah. good.

595
00:21:52.269 --> 00:21:53.686
You sure?

596
00:21:53.687 --> 00:21:56.772
Doesn't seem like Robby's
all that happy I'm back.

597
00:21:56.773 --> 00:21:59.400
Well. he's not going to be here.

598
00:21:59.401 --> 00:22:01.193
and I'm happy you're back.

599
00:22:01.194 --> 00:22:03.071
Thanks.

600
00:22:07.451 --> 00:22:11.580
Head and neck CT is negative.
except for mandible fracture.

601
00:22:12.539 --> 00:22:13.914
OK. let's get him off the board.

602
00:22:13.915 --> 00:22:15.207
Roll him. right side up.

603
00:22:15.208 --> 00:22:16.918
Hey. we're gonna need
the cuffs off.

604
00:22:19.963 --> 00:22:22.798
Ready.
And 1. 2. 3.

605
00:22:22.799 --> 00:22:25.176
Ah. gentle.

606
00:22:25.177 --> 00:22:26.844
Dr. King. how are
the chest and belly?

607
00:22:26.845 --> 00:22:30.097
We have three
anterior rib fractures

608
00:22:30.098 --> 00:22:32.016
and a small pulmonary contusion.

609
00:22:32.017 --> 00:22:33.267
- Not too bad.
- Mm-mm.

610
00:22:33.268 --> 00:22:34.977
When do pulmonary
contusions peak?

611
00:22:34.978 --> 00:22:36.395
After a few hours.

612
00:22:36.396 --> 00:22:37.938
And do we always admit
for three-rib fractures?

613
00:22:37.939 --> 00:22:39.273
In the elderly. yes.

614
00:22:39.274 --> 00:22:41.067
but not if a patient
can manage the pain

615
00:22:41.068 --> 00:22:42.986
and doesn't need
supplemental oxygen.

616
00:22:44.279 --> 00:22:45.821
OK. he's really hurting here.

617
00:22:45.822 --> 00:22:47.490
You think you could set us up
with a serratus anterior

618
00:22:47.491 --> 00:22:48.699
- field block?
- No problem.

619
00:22:48.700 --> 00:22:50.826
Oh. as long as that's OK

620
00:22:50.827 --> 00:22:51.994
with Dr. Al-Hashimi.

621
00:22:51.995 --> 00:22:54.121
If the patient consents.

622
00:22:54.122 --> 00:22:58.000
Mr. Varney. we wanna give you
a shot to numb your broken ribs

623
00:22:58.001 --> 00:22:59.168
so you can breathe easier.

624
00:22:59.169 --> 00:23:00.419
Uh-huh.

625
00:23:00.420 --> 00:23:02.088
OK. get Mr. Varney
prepped and draped.

626
00:23:02.089 --> 00:23:03.672
Dr. Mohan. you're in charge.

627
00:23:03.673 --> 00:23:05.508
Let's identify the landmarks.

628
00:23:05.509 --> 00:23:06.593
Cuffs.

629
00:23:07.969 --> 00:23:09.637
Yeah. you can just
leave them off. man.

630
00:23:09.638 --> 00:23:12.556
He's clearly not moving
on his own.

631
00:23:12.557 --> 00:23:14.141
We follow protocol.

632
00:23:14.142 --> 00:23:17.437
for his safety and yours.

633
00:23:19.231 --> 00:23:20.898
Do you need to get that?

634
00:23:20.899 --> 00:23:23.734
Nope.
It's my mom.

635
00:23:23.735 --> 00:23:25.986
Ignore it.
Just ignore it.

636
00:23:25.987 --> 00:23:27.822
- Amen. sister.
- Forearm is numb.

637
00:23:27.823 --> 00:23:29.115
We can irrigate.

638
00:23:29.116 --> 00:23:30.699
If I ignore a problem
for long enough.

639
00:23:30.700 --> 00:23:32.326
it just goes away. right?

640
00:23:32.327 --> 00:23:34.578
I wish I could
ignore my deposition.

641
00:23:34.579 --> 00:23:36.831
That. you can't ignore.

642
00:23:36.832 --> 00:23:38.082
But you'll be fine.

643
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:39.625
What's up with you. Whitaker?

644
00:23:39.626 --> 00:23:41.127
Trouble in roomie land?

645
00:23:41.128 --> 00:23:42.670
No. not really.

646
00:23:42.671 --> 00:23:45.965
I think I overstepped
with Dr. Langdon earlier.

647
00:23:45.966 --> 00:23:47.216
Oh.

648
00:23:47.217 --> 00:23:49.844
He was trying to prescribe
a patient benzos.

649
00:23:49.845 --> 00:23:52.763
and I told Langdon that
it'd be better if I did it.

650
00:23:52.764 --> 00:23:54.223
Oof.

651
00:23:54.224 --> 00:23:56.600
Only because I was already
the assigned physician.

652
00:23:56.601 --> 00:23:58.436
But yeah. now I feel
like an asshole.

653
00:23:58.437 --> 00:23:59.687
Langdon's fine.

654
00:23:59.688 --> 00:24:02.064
He went to rehab.
he's working the steps.

655
00:24:02.065 --> 00:24:06.610
and hopefully
it's all behind him.

656
00:24:06.611 --> 00:24:08.320
Place the needle in-plane.

657
00:24:08.321 --> 00:24:10.197
superficial
to the serratus anterior.

658
00:24:10.198 --> 00:24:12.450
between it
and the latissimus dorsi.

659
00:24:12.451 --> 00:24:13.784
Mm-hmm.

660
00:24:13.785 --> 00:24:15.953
You can see the fluid
dissect and diffuse...

661
00:24:15.954 --> 00:24:17.288
Dr. Mohan. we need you.

662
00:24:17.289 --> 00:24:18.914
We've got two more rigs
from Westbridge

663
00:24:18.915 --> 00:24:21.125
pulling up right now.

664
00:24:21.126 --> 00:24:22.626
Go. We got this.

665
00:24:22.627 --> 00:24:23.627
Thanks.

666
00:24:23.628 --> 00:24:26.130
How we doing in here?

667
00:24:26.131 --> 00:24:29.758
Spiked a temp to 102.
gave Tylenol.

668
00:24:29.759 --> 00:24:31.510
Check out her leg.

669
00:24:31.511 --> 00:24:33.429
That is a definite bulla.

670
00:24:33.430 --> 00:24:34.889
Did surgery come down yet?

671
00:24:34.890 --> 00:24:36.640
- Not yet.
- I need surgery?

672
00:24:36.641 --> 00:24:37.725
Page them again.

673
00:24:37.726 --> 00:24:39.518
Surgery would be a last resort.

674
00:24:39.519 --> 00:24:41.854
We would like them to come down
and check out your leg

675
00:24:41.855 --> 00:24:44.440
in case we need to remove
this infected skin.

676
00:24:44.441 --> 00:24:45.941
I thought it was just
a little swelling

677
00:24:45.942 --> 00:24:46.902
'cause I'm on my feet all day.

678
00:24:48.862 --> 00:24:50.779
BP's down to 85 over 40.

679
00:24:50.780 --> 00:24:52.448
- How much LR is in?
- Full bolus.

680
00:24:52.449 --> 00:24:54.074
Do another liter
and then start Levophed.

681
00:24:54.075 --> 00:24:55.494
Titrate to a MAP of 65.

682
00:24:56.870 --> 00:24:58.412
Can someone please
tell me what's going on?

683
00:24:58.413 --> 00:24:59.497
Pulse ox down to 89.

684
00:24:59.498 --> 00:25:00.998
100% non-rebreather.

685
00:25:00.999 --> 00:25:04.043
Sometimes an infection
can cause your blood pressure

686
00:25:04.044 --> 00:25:06.962
to drop and lower the amount
of oxygen in your blood.

687
00:25:06.963 --> 00:25:08.130
Am I gonna be OK?

688
00:25:08.131 --> 00:25:09.340
We're doing everything
that we can

689
00:25:09.341 --> 00:25:10.633
to make sure that you are.

690
00:25:10.634 --> 00:25:11.843
Jesse.

691
00:25:14.262 --> 00:25:15.638
What's up?

692
00:25:15.639 --> 00:25:16.972
Be ready to intubate
if you need to.

693
00:25:16.973 --> 00:25:18.474
- You want me to call Langdon?
- No.

694
00:25:18.475 --> 00:25:20.059
I will be right back.
and you can call surgery

695
00:25:20.060 --> 00:25:21.769
and tell them to get
their heads out of their asses

696
00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:23.355
and get down here.

697
00:25:31.905 --> 00:25:33.322
Did you bring Langdon back here?

698
00:25:33.323 --> 00:25:35.074
No. Al-Hashimi did.

699
00:25:35.075 --> 00:25:36.450
You banished him
to scut purgatory.

700
00:25:36.451 --> 00:25:37.618
He did everything
you would've done

701
00:25:37.619 --> 00:25:39.245
with that cellulitis patient.

702
00:25:39.246 --> 00:25:40.746
If you think he missed
something. tell him.

703
00:25:40.747 --> 00:25:42.331
Well. we're probably
gonna need to intubate.

704
00:25:42.332 --> 00:25:43.916
We're definitely
gonna need an ICU bed.

705
00:25:43.917 --> 00:25:45.167
What happened?

706
00:25:45.168 --> 00:25:47.336
She is in septic shock.
on pressors.

707
00:25:47.337 --> 00:25:49.171
Open shoulder dislocation
is back.

708
00:25:49.172 --> 00:25:50.965
Westbridge shut down
all their ORs. so they told us

709
00:25:50.966 --> 00:25:52.800
- to bring them back here.
- You joking?

710
00:25:52.801 --> 00:25:53.801
This ain't the Radisson.

711
00:25:53.802 --> 00:25:55.010
Not my problem.

712
00:25:55.011 --> 00:25:56.554
- Where should we park him?
- Grab a wall.

713
00:25:56.555 --> 00:25:57.972
Call Noelle. Call ortho.

714
00:25:57.973 --> 00:25:59.265
Call the OR and tell them
we got a patient back

715
00:25:59.266 --> 00:26:00.808
that needs surgery
and admission.

716
00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:02.810
Hey. so sorry
about this ambulance tour

717
00:26:02.811 --> 00:26:04.812
of Allegheny County.
Mr. Billings.

718
00:26:04.813 --> 00:26:06.438
but we got you from here.
I promise.

719
00:26:06.439 --> 00:26:07.815
Yeah. I'm starving.

720
00:26:07.816 --> 00:26:09.316
Is there any way I can
get something to eat?

721
00:26:09.317 --> 00:26:11.151
Sorry. not before surgery.

722
00:26:11.152 --> 00:26:12.403
Can I have a visitor?

723
00:26:12.404 --> 00:26:13.904
Sure.

724
00:26:13.905 --> 00:26:15.698
Any word from Gloria about
what's going on at Westbridge?

725
00:26:15.699 --> 00:26:17.324
Radio silence
from the ivory tower.

726
00:26:17.325 --> 00:26:18.993
And the charge nurse
over there isn't responding.

727
00:26:18.994 --> 00:26:20.619
Must be bad.

728
00:26:20.620 --> 00:26:21.996
I wonder if it's something that
security needs to know about.

729
00:26:21.997 --> 00:26:23.497
I'll keep you posted.

730
00:26:23.498 --> 00:26:25.291
Hey. you're kind of buds
with Gloria.

731
00:26:25.292 --> 00:26:26.584
Did she say anything
to you about what's

732
00:26:26.585 --> 00:26:28.335
- happening at Westbridge?
- No. You?

733
00:26:28.336 --> 00:26:30.879
Nope.
How are your patients?

734
00:26:30.880 --> 00:26:33.299
Our prisoner. Gus.
has stable injuries.

735
00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:35.509
and our law student
in Central 10 is awake.

736
00:26:35.510 --> 00:26:37.720
normal LP.
and awaiting a psych consult.

737
00:26:37.721 --> 00:26:39.054
Good.

738
00:26:39.055 --> 00:26:40.723
Quicker we can treat 'em.
street 'em. move 'em

739
00:26:40.724 --> 00:26:42.182
up the food chain. the better.

740
00:26:42.183 --> 00:26:44.268
Question.

741
00:26:44.269 --> 00:26:48.522
Why are you treating me
like one of your residents?

742
00:26:48.523 --> 00:26:49.732
I'm not.

743
00:26:49.733 --> 00:26:51.525
As the attending.
I like to know the status

744
00:26:51.526 --> 00:26:53.277
of all the patients
and doctors in the ED

745
00:26:53.278 --> 00:26:55.571
in case I need
to jump in quickly.

746
00:26:55.572 --> 00:26:56.572
Makes sense.

747
00:26:56.573 --> 00:26:58.991
Now your turn.

748
00:26:58.992 --> 00:27:00.326
What?

749
00:27:00.327 --> 00:27:02.453
As your fellow attending
in our ED.

750
00:27:02.454 --> 00:27:04.246
it only makes sense
for me to know the status

751
00:27:04.247 --> 00:27:06.332
of all the patients
and all the doctors

752
00:27:06.333 --> 00:27:09.877
in case I need to jump in
on a moment's notice.

753
00:27:09.878 --> 00:27:11.338
Touché.

754
00:27:14.049 --> 00:27:16.675
You have a non-displaced
fracture. distal tibia.

755
00:27:16.676 --> 00:27:18.844
So if you look at the bone
here. it's pretty well aligned.

756
00:27:18.845 --> 00:27:20.220
Sorry.
Hi.

757
00:27:20.221 --> 00:27:22.598
Hi. I was in the shower.
and I came as soon

758
00:27:22.599 --> 00:27:23.724
as I got Paul's message.

759
00:27:23.725 --> 00:27:25.351
- Lena?
- Hi.

760
00:27:25.352 --> 00:27:27.227
What happened?

761
00:27:27.228 --> 00:27:28.687
I had a seizure.

762
00:27:28.688 --> 00:27:30.314
You load her with Keppra?

763
00:27:30.315 --> 00:27:31.690
Yeah.

764
00:27:31.691 --> 00:27:33.692
Yeah. she's back
to baseline mental status.

765
00:27:33.693 --> 00:27:35.944
I'm sorry. I'm confused.
Aren't you off duty?

766
00:27:35.945 --> 00:27:39.114
- I'm Roxie's death doula.
- Oh.

767
00:27:39.115 --> 00:27:40.824
Her... her what?

768
00:27:40.825 --> 00:27:42.826
I help advocate
for people like Roxie

769
00:27:42.827 --> 00:27:45.829
to make their transition to
death a more peaceful process.

770
00:27:45.830 --> 00:27:48.832
It's like a birth doula
but for the end of life.

771
00:27:48.833 --> 00:27:52.461
She's been a real lifesaver
for our family.

772
00:27:52.462 --> 00:27:55.297
My husband cracking jokes
while I'm dying.

773
00:27:55.298 --> 00:27:57.049
See why I married him?

774
00:27:57.050 --> 00:27:58.884
Whatever you have to say
about my condition.

775
00:27:58.885 --> 00:28:00.803
you can share with Lena too.

776
00:28:00.804 --> 00:28:02.763
We were just
explaining that Roxie

777
00:28:02.764 --> 00:28:05.933
has a pathological fracture
through a metastatic lesion.

778
00:28:05.934 --> 00:28:07.476
Can you fix that?

779
00:28:07.477 --> 00:28:10.312
The bones are well aligned.
so she won't need surgery.

780
00:28:10.313 --> 00:28:11.772
The treatment is immobilization

781
00:28:11.773 --> 00:28:12.940
and a long leg boot.

782
00:28:12.941 --> 00:28:14.692
Oh!

783
00:28:14.693 --> 00:28:16.235
Maybe we up her pain meds.

784
00:28:16.236 --> 00:28:17.778
Yeah. sure.

785
00:28:17.779 --> 00:28:19.154
We can do that.

786
00:28:19.155 --> 00:28:21.448
The bones should heal
in about six weeks.

787
00:28:21.449 --> 00:28:23.993
If I live that long.

788
00:28:25.912 --> 00:28:26.954
<i>Still numb here?</i>

789
00:28:26.955 --> 00:28:28.539
Yeah. bro.

790
00:28:28.540 --> 00:28:30.874
Great.

791
00:28:30.875 --> 00:28:32.751
You think it's
gonna leave a scar?

792
00:28:32.752 --> 00:28:36.797
I don't think it.
I know it.

793
00:28:36.798 --> 00:28:38.590
Holy shit.

794
00:28:38.591 --> 00:28:40.134
Fuck are you doing here?

795
00:28:40.135 --> 00:28:41.135
