- It's OK.

817
00:29:24.179 --> 00:29:27.848
Doc said it's gonna take
some time. but it'll heal OK.

818
00:29:27.849 --> 00:29:29.391
Awesome.

819
00:29:29.392 --> 00:29:31.185
So maybe we can try again
in a couple of months or...

820
00:29:31.186 --> 00:29:32.604
No.

821
00:29:34.063 --> 00:29:35.732
OK. bag her.

822
00:29:37.776 --> 00:29:39.234
Yellow on the end-tidal.

823
00:29:39.235 --> 00:29:40.986
- Sorry. got backed up.
- Sounds a little wet.

824
00:29:40.987 --> 00:29:42.112
Someone asked
for a surgical consult?

825
00:29:42.113 --> 00:29:43.363
That's because all the fluid.

826
00:29:43.364 --> 00:29:44.782
TKO the lines for now.

827
00:29:44.783 --> 00:29:47.117
Vent settings 50%.
tidal volume 500. AC 12?

828
00:29:47.118 --> 00:29:48.494
Yep. that's perfect.

829
00:29:48.495 --> 00:29:49.828
Surgery here.
Hello.

830
00:29:49.829 --> 00:29:51.413
Hey. it's about time.
Where's Garcia?

831
00:29:51.414 --> 00:29:53.248
Stuck in the ER.
She sent me down. What you got?

832
00:29:53.249 --> 00:29:54.708
Septic shock.
respiratory failure.

833
00:29:54.709 --> 00:29:56.376
and possible
necrotizing fasciitis.

834
00:29:56.377 --> 00:29:58.128
She needs to go to the OR ASAP.

835
00:29:58.129 --> 00:30:00.380
The infection was isolated
to the dorsum of the foot

836
00:30:00.381 --> 00:30:02.007
five hours ago. but now
we're almost to the knee

837
00:30:02.008 --> 00:30:03.675
with bullae.
crepitus. and edema.

838
00:30:03.676 --> 00:30:05.344
- Yeah.
- You seen nec fasc before?

839
00:30:05.345 --> 00:30:06.553
In a textbook.

840
00:30:06.554 --> 00:30:08.681
I was a med student
two weeks ago.

841
00:30:10.558 --> 00:30:13.143
- Gotta show this to Dr. Garcia.
- OK. OK. Jesus Christ.

842
00:30:13.144 --> 00:30:14.812
Go get anybody else
from your service down here...

843
00:30:14.813 --> 00:30:16.104
Shamsi. Miller. Walsh...

844
00:30:16.105 --> 00:30:17.231
I don't know any
of this people. but...

845
00:30:17.232 --> 00:30:18.607
Don't take this personally.

846
00:30:18.608 --> 00:30:21.652
I just need a fucking grown-up
down here.

847
00:30:21.653 --> 00:30:23.612
Nice job on the sub-Qs.

848
00:30:23.613 --> 00:30:25.364
Really took the tension
off the wound.

849
00:30:25.365 --> 00:30:26.448
Thanks.

850
00:30:26.449 --> 00:30:28.116
I can help with the skin layer.

851
00:30:28.117 --> 00:30:30.078
Four hands are faster than two.

852
00:30:32.539 --> 00:30:33.956
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

853
00:30:33.957 --> 00:30:36.291
That just tore
right through the skin.

854
00:30:36.292 --> 00:30:37.626
You may need to take
bigger bites

855
00:30:37.627 --> 00:30:39.336
farther away
from the wound edges.

856
00:30:39.337 --> 00:30:41.672
Yep.

857
00:30:41.673 --> 00:30:44.968
Skin seems pretty fragile.

858
00:30:49.097 --> 00:30:50.556
Oh.

859
00:30:50.557 --> 00:30:52.224
Yeah. this is not working.

860
00:30:52.225 --> 00:30:54.184
He has the skin strength
of an 80-year-old.

861
00:30:54.185 --> 00:30:56.353
Put down Steri-Strips
with benzoin.

862
00:30:56.354 --> 00:30:59.648
not across the wound but along
each wound edge. both sides.

863
00:30:59.649 --> 00:31:01.191
It'll hold the sutures.

864
00:31:01.192 --> 00:31:04.653
- Yup.
- What say you. Dr. Robby?

865
00:31:04.654 --> 00:31:06.613
Great. MacGyver move.

866
00:31:06.614 --> 00:31:09.533
Go for it.

867
00:31:09.534 --> 00:31:13.287
Does a Dr. MacGyver
work here?

868
00:31:13.288 --> 00:31:15.789
I don't know.

869
00:31:15.790 --> 00:31:17.749
The patient symptoms
are consistent with lumbar

870
00:31:17.750 --> 00:31:21.712
radiculopathy at L4. L5. most
likely due to disc herniation.

871
00:31:21.713 --> 00:31:23.213
Coughing patient
admitted to isolation

872
00:31:23.214 --> 00:31:25.173
for verified medication
administration

873
00:31:25.174 --> 00:31:26.550
and started on RIPE therapy.

874
00:31:26.551 --> 00:31:28.093
Yeah. why do I even bother?

875
00:31:28.094 --> 00:31:29.136
Just fail me now.

876
00:31:29.137 --> 00:31:30.304
OK.

877
00:31:30.305 --> 00:31:31.805
Get in touch
with a social worker.

878
00:31:31.806 --> 00:31:33.307
They're gonna wanna
do contact tracing

879
00:31:33.308 --> 00:31:35.142
and help her figure out
transitional housing

880
00:31:35.143 --> 00:31:36.518
for when she's discharged.

881
00:31:36.519 --> 00:31:37.853
Got it.

882
00:31:37.854 --> 00:31:39.813
And make sure
infection control responded.

883
00:31:39.814 --> 00:31:41.273
The people in the waiting room
could have been exposed.

884
00:31:41.274 --> 00:31:44.610
They need to be
notified and tested.

885
00:31:44.611 --> 00:31:45.861
OK.

886
00:31:45.862 --> 00:31:48.780
Relax.

887
00:31:48.781 --> 00:31:51.033
You can take the mask off.
You don't have TB.

888
00:31:51.034 --> 00:31:54.161
At least not yet.

889
00:31:54.162 --> 00:31:56.747
Oh. great.

890
00:31:56.748 --> 00:31:59.666
This is fucked up.

891
00:31:59.667 --> 00:32:01.960
How are you so calm?

892
00:32:01.961 --> 00:32:03.629
Expected job hazard.

893
00:32:03.630 --> 00:32:04.880
You get used to it.

894
00:32:04.881 --> 00:32:06.465
Yeah. no. thanks.

895
00:32:06.466 --> 00:32:09.051
70% of doctors in training
at urban hospitals

896
00:32:09.052 --> 00:32:11.386
get exposed to TB
and wind up on meds.

897
00:32:11.387 --> 00:32:13.722
- Jesus.
- Mm-hmm.

898
00:32:13.723 --> 00:32:16.099
They don't teach you that
in med school.

899
00:32:16.100 --> 00:32:18.268
Mrs. Randolph's back.

900
00:32:18.269 --> 00:32:20.145
Pulled up her X-ray.

901
00:32:20.146 --> 00:32:21.313
OK.

902
00:32:21.314 --> 00:32:23.440
No volvulus.
no air fluid levels.

903
00:32:23.441 --> 00:32:26.026
What do you think of this?

904
00:32:26.027 --> 00:32:28.111
Fecal material?

905
00:32:28.112 --> 00:32:29.821
A shit ton.

906
00:32:29.822 --> 00:32:31.448
Sorry. had to be said.

907
00:32:31.449 --> 00:32:33.033
So. what. she needs an enema?

908
00:32:33.034 --> 00:32:34.618
No.
Tried and failed. remember?

909
00:32:34.619 --> 00:32:35.619
Yeah.

910
00:32:35.620 --> 00:32:37.287
Time to dig in.

911
00:32:37.288 --> 00:32:38.914
How are we gonna do that?

912
00:32:38.915 --> 00:32:42.835
Oh. there is no "we"
in disimpaction.

913
00:32:47.799 --> 00:32:50.050
I haven't done one before.

914
00:32:50.051 --> 00:32:53.011
Shouldn't I observe first?

915
00:32:53.012 --> 00:32:55.556
I know just the guy
to teach you.

916
00:33:04.816 --> 00:33:07.651
I spoke to the charge nurse
in med-surg.

917
00:33:07.652 --> 00:33:08.944
They can take Orlando today.

918
00:33:08.945 --> 00:33:10.737
- Yes!
- That's wonderful.

919
00:33:10.738 --> 00:33:12.322
They know he's
on an insulin drip?

920
00:33:12.323 --> 00:33:14.866
They know. and they can
change to a SQUID protocol.

921
00:33:14.867 --> 00:33:15.867
SQUID?

922
00:33:15.868 --> 00:33:17.619
Sub-Q insulin in DKA.

923
00:33:17.620 --> 00:33:19.329
So no IV drip?

924
00:33:19.330 --> 00:33:22.124
Just shots of short-acting
insulin every four hours prn.

925
00:33:22.125 --> 00:33:25.544
The med-surg nurses have time
to check a glucose every hour?

926
00:33:25.545 --> 00:33:26.545
They say so.

927
00:33:26.546 --> 00:33:28.588
And five days on med-surge

928
00:33:28.589 --> 00:33:32.342
is gonna cut your hospital bill
down by 2/3.

929
00:33:32.343 --> 00:33:34.219
OK.

930
00:33:34.220 --> 00:33:36.096
So what's that gonna cost?

931
00:33:36.097 --> 00:33:37.514
Well. I can't give you
an exact amount.

932
00:33:37.515 --> 00:33:39.599
but roughly $35.000.

933
00:33:39.600 --> 00:33:42.728
So after about 40%.
I'll still have to pay.

934
00:33:42.729 --> 00:33:44.563
what. like. 20 grand?

935
00:33:44.564 --> 00:33:46.815
The hospital can work out
a payment plan.

936
00:33:46.816 --> 00:33:48.525
Orlando. we'll be OK.

937
00:33:48.526 --> 00:33:50.068
We'll figure it out.

938
00:33:50.069 --> 00:33:52.529
I'll take on extra shifts
