your rectum so that we can

1001
00:36:17.675 --> 00:36:19.176
get your bowels moving again.

1002
00:36:19.177 --> 00:36:20.177
I know.

1003
00:36:20.178 --> 00:36:22.929
Here we go.

1004
00:36:22.930 --> 00:36:26.057
Mrs. Randolph.
I would like you to relax

1005
00:36:26.058 --> 00:36:28.977
like you're having
a bowel movement.

1006
00:36:28.978 --> 00:36:31.563
Nice and deep.

1007
00:36:31.564 --> 00:36:33.857
OK.

1008
00:36:33.858 --> 00:36:38.069
Curve the finger
like an ice cream scoop.

1009
00:36:38.070 --> 00:36:42.699
And bring it out.

1010
00:36:42.700 --> 00:36:44.452
You're up. Ogilvie.

1011
00:36:48.748 --> 00:36:50.957
Some more pressure.
Mrs. Randolph.

1012
00:36:50.958 --> 00:36:52.418
I'm ready.

1013
00:36:59.175 --> 00:37:03.303
And here I thought
you weren't a quick study.

1014
00:37:03.304 --> 00:37:05.222
Keep going.

1015
00:37:05.223 --> 00:37:07.432
Mrs. Randolph.
in order to prevent this

1016
00:37:07.433 --> 00:37:08.850
from happening again.
I think you

1017
00:37:08.851 --> 00:37:10.435
need a better stool softener.

1018
00:37:10.436 --> 00:37:11.978
You can try MiraLAX.

1019
00:37:11.979 --> 00:37:14.522
Just a tablespoon with a big
glass of water every morning

1020
00:37:14.523 --> 00:37:15.523
should do the trick.

1021
00:37:15.524 --> 00:37:16.651
OK.

1022
00:37:18.945 --> 00:37:19.945
Oh.

1023
00:37:19.946 --> 00:37:21.529
Sorry.

1024
00:37:21.530 --> 00:37:22.697
Passing gas is good.

1025
00:37:22.698 --> 00:37:24.407
Means we're making progress.

1026
00:37:24.408 --> 00:37:26.117
Does that mean that I can...
I can stop?

1027
00:37:26.118 --> 00:37:27.870
No. Nope.
Keep going.

1028
00:37:32.917 --> 00:37:36.169
OK. Ogilvie. you...
you might wanna...

1029
00:37:36.170 --> 00:37:37.880
Oh!

1030
00:37:41.759 --> 00:37:43.261
Much better.

1031
00:37:44.303 --> 00:37:46.304
MAP's holding on Levophed.

1032
00:37:46.305 --> 00:37:48.265
1 mike per kg per minute.

1033
00:37:48.266 --> 00:37:49.474
Do me a favor.

1034
00:37:49.475 --> 00:37:50.684
Give me some 4x4s
on some Betadine.

1035
00:37:50.685 --> 00:37:51.977
Sorry. we're getting killed

1036
00:37:51.978 --> 00:37:53.395
with transfers from Westbridge.

1037
00:37:53.396 --> 00:37:55.563
Mesenteric ischemia.
perforated bowel.

1038
00:37:55.564 --> 00:37:56.564
Got a hot one here.

1039
00:37:56.565 --> 00:37:57.565
Yeah.

1040
00:37:57.566 --> 00:37:58.692
Possible nec fasc.

1041
00:37:58.693 --> 00:38:00.068
Possible?

1042
00:38:00.069 --> 00:38:01.444
Need CT with contrast
to confirm.

1043
00:38:01.445 --> 00:38:03.154
This is spreading like wildfire.

1044
00:38:03.155 --> 00:38:04.531
By the time you get your CT.
it's gonna be up to her waist.

1045
00:38:04.532 --> 00:38:05.615
She's gonna need
a hemicorporectomy.

1046
00:38:05.616 --> 00:38:06.950
She needs a CT scan.

1047
00:38:06.951 --> 00:38:09.619
How about
a stainless steel scan?

1048
00:38:09.620 --> 00:38:11.830
For Christ's sake.
Robinavitch!

1049
00:38:11.831 --> 00:38:15.292
Robby. what the fuck
are you doing?

1050
00:38:15.293 --> 00:38:17.002
Oh. God. I think I might puke.

1051
00:38:17.003 --> 00:38:19.462
That's called dirty dishwater
exudate without purulence.

1052
00:38:19.463 --> 00:38:21.673
There's a gray appearance
to the fascia. and in the OR.

1053
00:38:21.674 --> 00:38:23.883
you'll see easy separation
in the tissue planes.

1054
00:38:23.884 --> 00:38:25.218
When do you start
your sabbatical?

1055
00:38:25.219 --> 00:38:26.970
- Tomorrow.
- Not a moment too soon.

1056
00:38:26.971 --> 00:38:28.889
Thanks for coming down.

1057
00:38:32.101 --> 00:38:35.687
I'm catching up on my
charting as fast as I can.

1058
00:38:35.688 --> 00:38:38.565
Why don't you give
my generative AI app a try?

1059
00:38:38.566 --> 00:38:41.067
It's 30% more efficient.
and providers report

1060
00:38:41.068 --> 00:38:42.944
increased job satisfaction.

1061
00:38:42.945 --> 00:38:45.947
And you'll rarely have to stay
overtime to complete charts.

1062
00:38:45.948 --> 00:38:47.699
Yeah?

1063
00:38:47.700 --> 00:38:48.992
OK.

1064
00:38:48.993 --> 00:38:50.577
Yeah. I'm usually here
at least a couple hours

1065
00:38:50.578 --> 00:38:52.454
after every shift
trying to catch up. so...

1066
00:38:52.455 --> 00:38:54.873
Sure. AI will make
doctors more efficient.

1067
00:38:54.874 --> 00:38:57.167
but hospitals will expect us
to treat more patients

1068
00:38:57.168 --> 00:38:59.169
without any extra pay.
of course.

1069
00:38:59.170 --> 00:39:00.962
all the while eliminating
staff positions

1070
00:39:00.963 --> 00:39:02.672
for attending and residents.

1071
00:39:02.673 --> 00:39:04.257
Oh. Dr. Robby.
I am not an advocate

1072
00:39:04.258 --> 00:39:06.384
for erasing my own profession.

1073
00:39:06.385 --> 00:39:09.888
But I am advocating for getting
to spend more time with my son.

1074
00:39:09.889 --> 00:39:12.849
Nothing can replace family.

1075
00:39:12.850 --> 00:39:14.851
What's the status
of your septic patient?

1076
00:39:14.852 --> 00:39:17.645
Nec fasc.
Surgery's taking her up.

1077
00:39:17.646 --> 00:39:20.190
Think they'll be able
to save her leg?

1078
00:39:20.191 --> 00:39:22.150
Right now. I'm just hoping
they can save her life.

1079
00:39:22.151 --> 00:39:24.736
Hey. how's Ogilvie doing?

1080
00:39:24.737 --> 00:39:28.573
A little TB exposure.
a touch of ass-plosion.

1081
00:39:28.574 --> 00:39:30.700
All in all.
pretty good day so far.

1082
00:39:30.701 --> 00:39:31.993
Kaison. you came.

1083
00:39:31.994 --> 00:39:33.536
Hey. ain't no way
I was gonna let you

1084
00:39:33.537 --> 00:39:35.455
miss Peter and Aubrey's
epic Fourth of July party.

1085
00:39:35.456 --> 00:39:37.665
Come on. now. Hey.

1086
00:39:37.666 --> 00:39:39.334
Brought some brew.

1087
00:39:39.335 --> 00:39:40.710
Oh. you are the man.

1088
00:39:40.711 --> 00:39:42.170
Appreciate
the bromance over here.

1089
00:39:42.171 --> 00:39:44.506
but no food 'cause you
might go into surgery.

1090
00:39:44.507 --> 00:39:47.093
And no beer 'cause we're
a goddamn hospital.

1091
00:39:50.721 --> 00:39:52.931
Starting your sabbatical early?

1092
00:39:52.932 --> 00:39:54.766
I know someone who could
really use a drink right now.

1093
00:39:54.767 --> 00:39:56.059
In the hospital?

1094
00:39:56.060 --> 00:39:58.479
As a parting gift.

1095
00:40:02.525 --> 00:40:04.150
How's it looking?

1096
00:40:04.151 --> 00:40:05.402
Good.

1097
00:40:05.403 --> 00:40:07.362
The Steri-Strips did the trick.

1098
00:40:07.363 --> 00:40:08.488
CT's ready.

1099
00:40:08.489 --> 00:40:10.115
We already scanned him.

1100
00:40:10.116 --> 00:40:12.492
Head and neck want thin cuts
and a 3D reconstruction

1101
00:40:12.493 --> 00:40:14.494
of the mandible
before they decide

1102
00:40:14.495 --> 00:40:15.954
if Mr. Varney needs surgery.

1103
00:40:15.955 --> 00:40:17.872
Have they even come down
to examine him in person?

1104
00:40:17.873 --> 00:40:19.457
No. they must be backed up.

1105
00:40:19.458 --> 00:40:23.253
Or there's a July Fourth sale
at the BMW dealership.

1106
00:40:23.254 --> 00:40:24.546
Labs are back.

1107
00:40:24.547 --> 00:40:26.381
Albumin's low.
Total protein's low.

1108
00:40:26.382 --> 00:40:27.966
He also has
megaloblastic anemia.

1109
00:40:27.967 --> 00:40:29.217
- Malnutrition.
- Probably.

1110
00:40:29.218 --> 00:40:30.385
Jail cuisine.

1111
00:40:30.386 --> 00:40:31.761
Whitaker.
what labs should we add?

1112
00:40:31.762 --> 00:40:33.888
B12. folate. iron levels.

1113
00:40:33.889 --> 00:40:35.390
Good.

1114
00:40:35.391 --> 00:40:37.016
We're gonna run some more
tests. Mr. Varney.

1115
00:40:37.017 --> 00:40:38.352
Hang in there.

1116
00:40:42.982 --> 00:40:45.483
I have to pee.

1117
00:40:45.484 --> 00:40:46.943
There's no PureWick here.

1118
00:40:46.944 --> 00:40:48.194
But here you go. hon.

1119
00:40:48.195 --> 00:40:50.155
- I'll help you get on.
- No. No.

1120
00:40:50.156 --> 00:40:52.574
No bedpan.
I can walk to the bathroom.

1121
00:40:52.575 --> 00:40:54.242
- I just need a little help.
- Are you sure?

1122
00:40:54.243 --> 00:40:55.326
I'm here. babe.

1123
00:40:55.327 --> 00:40:56.828
Oh. we got this Mr. Hamler.

1124
00:40:56.829 --> 00:41:00.081
You'll have to bring
your IV and portable oxygen.

1125
00:41:00.082 --> 00:41:02.083
Please?

1126
00:41:02.084 --> 00:41:04.502
I'll grab a wheelchair.

1127
00:41:04.503 --> 00:41:06.463
Let's try to sit you up
and dangle your legs.

1128
00:41:06.464 --> 00:41:07.923
OK.

1129
00:41:10.634 --> 00:41:13.971
1. 2. 3.

1130
00:41:19.685 --> 00:41:21.394
This is not a good idea.

1131
00:41:21.395 --> 00:41:23.521
I don't think
we're gonna need this.

1132
00:41:23.522 --> 00:41:25.148
Hey. Paul. Paul.

1133
00:41:25.149 --> 00:41:27.317
why don't you come
grab a cup of coffee with me?

1134
00:41:27.318 --> 00:41:29.277
I'm still zonked
from my all-nighter.

1135
00:41:29.278 --> 00:41:32.947
and I wanna go over some
delivery instructions with you.

1136
00:41:32.948 --> 00:41:35.617
Sure.

1137
00:41:35.618 --> 00:41:37.494
Rox. you OK?

1138
00:41:37.495 --> 00:41:40.331
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah. It's OK.

1139
00:41:47.046 --> 00:41:49.006
Bedpan it is.

1140
00:41:57.014 --> 00:41:58.807
You lose your pulse ox again. bud?

1141
00:42:04.438 --> 00:42:05.855
Louie.

1142
00:42:05.856 --> 00:42:07.732
Louie!

1143
00:42:07.733 --> 00:42:10.318
He kept pulling off
his pulse ox.

1144
00:42:10.319 --> 00:42:11.736
It's on.
It's at 71.

1145
00:42:11.737 --> 00:42:13.155
Louie. wake up.

1146
00:42:14.782 --> 00:42:16.574
- I'm not getting a carotid.
- I got the airway.

1147
00:42:16.575 --> 00:42:19.662
Hey. Perlah. crash cart.
intubation tray. please.

1147
